Afgri, IFCA, Kumba, SABMiller, Vodacom: South African Stock Market Preview

-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 
2011-07-20T22:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/afgri-kumba-sabmiller-vodacom-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index fell for the first day
in two, easing 2.62, or less than 0.1 percent, to 32,056.06 by
the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  Afgri Ltd. (AFR)  : The handler of about a third of South
Africa’s grain said earnings per share for the year to June 30
will be 35 percent to 45 percent lower. The stock dropped 2.6
percent to 6.89 rand.  Hulamin Ltd. (HLM)  : Africa’s largest aluminum processor
holds its annual general meeting. The stock slid 1.3 percent to
7.40 rand.  IFCA Technologies Ltd. (IFC)  : The investment company
with interests in software solutions and services holds its
annual general meeting. IFCA closed unchanged at 7 cents.  IQuad Group Ltd. (IQG)  : The financial-services company
holds its annual general meeting. The stock climbed 3.6 percent
to 2.90 rand.  Kumba Iron Ore Ltd. (KIO)  : The producer of the steel-
making ingredient releases results for the six months to end
June 2011. Net earnings for the period were expected to rise 42
percent to 9.2 billion rand over the comparable period a year
earlier, the group said in a trading statement on July 7. The
stock gained 1.2 percent to 525 rand.  SABMiller Plc. (SAB)  , the world’s second-largest brewer
by volume, holds its annual general meeting. The stock added 0.2
percent to 256.51 rand.  Vodacom Group Ltd. (VOD)  : The largest provider of
mobile-phone services to South Africans releases its first-
quarter update. The stock rose 0.9 percent to 87.81 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Gunnion in Johannesburg at 
 sgunnion@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
